name: overture-graphics-plugin
description: Live plotting for Overture using listeners

releases.body:
# Changelog

**Issue(s) fixed:**
- No longer shows variables that are not subscribable (non-number variables).

**New feature(s):**
- Shows data type of variables in variable dropdown.
- Added support for subscribing to an entire lists at once. (NB: New elements are not added after plot creation).

releases.name: Update
releases.body:
# Changelog

**Issue(s) fixed:**
- OS X: Menu not displaying app name.
- OS X: Application not being able to connect.
- OS X: Quit from application menu not reacting.

**New feature(s):**
- Loading and saving config file is now possible through file dialogs.

releases.name: Feature-complete
releases.body:
**Fixed issue(s):**
- RemoteIntepreter no longer keeps running after closing Electron app.

releases.name: v 1.0.4
releases.body:
**Added support for:**
- Manual selection of root class and world run method
- Saving/loading configurations (consisting of root class, run method and plots)
- Multiple variables in same plot
- Multiple plot types (2d/3d/list)

releases.name: Release v 1.0.2
releases.body:
- fixed missing nat + nat1 support
- removed status dump

releases.name: TEMPO Plotting Tool
releases.body:
2D plotting tool using variable listeners on VDM models.

**Features:**
- Create new 2D plots
- Subscribe to variable from model
- Start model from plotting application
- Auto-update 2D plots

**The release includes:**
- The jar with Remote Control for overture
  - overture-plotting-tool-0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar
- The plotting tool application
  - tempo-ui-{PLATFORM}.zip
- An example overture project using Remote Control and a simple model
  - Tempo-Example.zip
